window.ICML_PAPERS["54101"] = [{"id":"NkgEKRCiyZ","en":"Certified Characterization of Privacy, Participation, and Convergence in Over-the-Air Federated Learning","ko":"무선 federated learning에서 privacy, participation, convergence의 인증된 특성화","authors":"Ayse Sila Okcu, O. Tansel Baydas, Ozgur B. Akan","abs":"<p>Over-the-air federated learning (OTA-FL) exploits wireless superposition to aggregate client updates in one transmission, reducing communication overhead. In truncated channel-inversion OTA-FL, the receive scaling factor $\\eta$ jointly controls normalized channel noise, privacy sensitivity, and client activation thresholds. We characterize this coupling for smooth nonconvex objectives under Rayleigh fading via certified truncation envelopes. The resulting bounds yield a computable feasible set of receive amplitudes satisfying convergence, privacy, and participation constraints. We show that apparent participation fairness can be misleading at large $\\eta$, where clients may be nearly uniformly excluded, and introduce a dropped-weight constraint to rule out this degenerate regime. We further propose CARES, an adaptive receive-scaling algorithm that selects $\\eta_t$ online via contextual bandits, tracks privacy with zero-concentrated differential privacy, and enforces participation-envelope constraints. Experiments on image classification show that CARES achieves competitive accuracy and strong worst-client accuracy while maintaining formal $(\\varepsilon,\\delta)$-DP using only implicit channel noise among the OTA baselines considered.</p>","absKo":"Over-the-air federated learning(OTA-FL)은 무선 superposition을 활용해 한 번의 전송으로 client update를 집계함으로써 통신 오버헤드를 줄인다. truncated channel-inversion OTA-FL에서 receive scaling factor $\\eta$는 normalized channel noise, privacy sensitivity, client activation threshold를 공동으로 제어한다. 우리는 certified truncation envelope를 통해 Rayleigh fading 하의 smooth nonconvex objective에 대해 이러한 결합을 특성화한다. 그 결과로 얻는 bound는 수렴, privacy, 참여 제약을 만족하는 수신 진폭의 계산 가능한 feasible set을 제공한다. 우리는 큰 $\\eta$에서는 client가 거의 균일하게 제외될 수 있어 겉보기 참여 공정성이 오해를 불러일으킬 수 있음을 보이고, 이러한 퇴화된 regime을 배제하기 위해 dropped-weight constraint를 도입한다. 더 나아가 우리는 CARES를 제안하는데, 이는 contextual bandit을 통해 온라인으로 $\\eta_t$를 선택하고, zero-concentrated differential privacy로 privacy를 추적하며, participation-envelope constraint를 강제하는 adaptive receive-scaling algorithm이다. 이미지 분류 실험에서 CARES는 고려한 OTA baseline 중 implicit channel noise만을 사용하면서도, 형식적 $(\\varepsilon,\\delta)$-DP를 유지한 채 경쟁력 있는 accuracy와 강한 worst-client accuracy를 달성한다.","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=NkgEKRCiyZ"},{"id":"tO2dUpPh5p","en":"Graph-Localized Offline Federated Multi-Agent Reinforcement Learning for Wireless Networks","ko":"무선 네트워크를 위한 그래프-지역화 오프라인 연합 다중 에이전트 강화학습","authors":"O. Tansel Baydas, Ayse Sila Okcu, Ozgur B. Akan","abs":"<p>Wireless networks motivate offline multi-agent reinforcement learning (MARL) as online exploration degrades service, and operator logs are rarely poolable across deployments. Existing offline MARL relies on global coverage that scales exponentially in the number of agents. We exploit the interaction graph induced by interference and contention to replace global coverage with $\\kappa$-hop neighborhood coverage: a client contributes to agent~$i$&#x27;s local estimator only if it observes $\\mathcal{N}_i^\\kappa$. We prove a localized offline policy guarantee whose error decomposes into a locality bias decaying exponentially in $\\kappa$, a near-neighbor shift bias, and a federated estimation term shrinking with the pooled observability-valid sample size. Our algorithm, F-GLOFF, matches a centralized raw-pooled oracle on multi-AP user association without sharing transitions and outperforms the engineered baselines by 12%.</p>","absKo":"무선 네트워크는 온라인 exploration이 서비스를 저하시키고 operator log는 배포 간에 pool하기 어렵기 때문에 offline multi-agent reinforcement learning(MARL)을 촉진한다. 기존의 offline MARL은 agent 수에 따라 지수적으로 커지는 global coverage에 의존한다. 우리는 interference와 contention이 유도하는 interaction graph를 활용하여 global coverage를 $\\kappa$-hop neighborhood coverage로 대체한다. 즉, client는 $\\mathcal{N}_i^\\kappa$를 관측할 때만 agent~$i$의 local estimator에 기여한다. 우리는 locality bias가 $\\kappa$에 따라 지수적으로 감소하고, near-neighbor shift bias와, pooled observability-valid sample size에 따라 줄어드는 federated estimation term으로 분해되는 localized offline policy guarantee를 증명한다. 우리의 알고리즘 F-GLOFF는 transition을 공유하지 않고도 multi-AP user association에서 centralized raw-pooled oracle과 동등한 성능을 보이며, engineered baseline보다 12% 더 뛰어나다.","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=tO2dUpPh5p"},{"id":"Qt2X2QxdjT","en":"Towards Edge-deployable Telecom Intelligence with Efficient Small Language Models","ko":"효율적인 작은 language model로 엣지 배포 가능한 telecom intelligence를 향하여","authors":"Somin Im, Heewon Park, Minhae Kwon","abs":"<p>Deployment of large language models in 6G and O-RAN edge environments is constrained by latency, hardware, and privacy requirements that make cloud-hosted inference impractical. While sub-2B small language models (SLMs) are suitable for local deployment, their general-purpose pretraining provides limited telecommunications-domain knowledge, and existing fine-tuning approaches overlook the diversity of knowledge areas and reasoning types the domain encompasses. We propose lightweight task-specific LoRA fine-tuning, training one compact adapter per task category over a shared frozen backbone, and evaluate on the GSMA ot-full benchmark across six task categories using three SLMs. Our results show that SLMs with lightweight LoRA adapters not only narrow the performance gap with larger models but occasionally surpass them, while each adapter introduces only a small fraction of additional parameters relative to the frozen backbone. These findings suggest that lightweight task-specific adaptation offers a practical and efficient path toward edge-native telecommunications intelligence.</p>","absKo":"6G 및 O-RAN edge 환경에 large language model을 배포하는 일은 latency, hardware, privacy 요구사항에 의해 제약되며, 이로 인해 cloud-hosted inference는 실용적이지 않다. 2B 미만의 small language model (SLM)은 local deployment에 적합하지만, 범용 pretraining은 telecommunications domain 지식이 제한적이며, 기존 fine-tuning 접근은 이 domain이 포괄하는 지식 영역과 reasoning 유형의 다양성을 충분히 반영하지 못한다. 우리는 공유된 frozen backbone 위에 task category마다 하나의 compact adapter를 학습하는 lightweight task-specific LoRA fine-tuning을 제안하고, 세 개의 SLM을 사용하여 여섯 개 task category에 걸친 GSMA ot-full benchmark에서 평가한다. 우리의 결과는 lightweight LoRA adapter를 장착한 SLM이 larger model과의 성능 격차를 좁힐 뿐 아니라 때때로 이를 능가하기도 하며, 각 adapter는 frozen backbone에 비해 추가 파라미터를 매우 적게만 도입함을 보여준다. 이러한 결과는 lightweight task-specific adaptation이 edge-native telecommunications intelligence를 향한 실용적이고 효율적인 경로임을 시사한다.","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=Qt2X2QxdjT"},{"id":"as9uoUepox","en":"A Tale of Two Learning Algorithms: Multiple Stream Random Walk and Asynchronous Gossip","ko":"두 가지 학습 알고리즘의 이야기: 다중 스트림 random walk와 비동기 gossip","authors":"Peyman Gholami, Hulya Seferoglu","abs":"<p>We investigate the relative performance of gossip and random walk-based decentralized learning algorithms across varying network topologies and data heterogeneities. To this end, we introduce “Multi-Walk,” an asynchronous multi-stream random walk algorithm, and comprehensively compare its convergence against “Asynchronous Gossip” in terms of computational iterations, wall-clock time, and communication overhead. Our analysis demonstrates that Multi-Walk achieves superior iteration convergence in large diameter graphs and consistently lower communication costs, except within small-diameter networks experiencing extreme data heterogeneity. Furthermore, both methods exhibit linear wall-clock speedups relative to the number of concurrent computations. These findings elucidate the inherent performance trade-offs between the two approaches, offering guidance on algorithm selection based on structural and distributional network conditions. Our codes are available for reproducibility.</p>","absKo":"우리는 서로 다른 network topology와 data heterogeneity 전반에서 gossip과 random walk 기반 decentralized learning algorithm의 상대적 성능을 조사한다. 이를 위해 우리는 “Multi-Walk”라는 asynchronous multi-stream random walk algorithm을 도입하고, computational iteration, wall-clock time, communication overhead 측면에서 “Asynchronous Gossip”과의 convergence를 포괄적으로 비교한다. 우리의 분석은 Multi-Walk가 large diameter graph에서 더 우수한 iteration convergence를 달성하고, small-diameter network에서 극단적인 data heterogeneity가 나타나는 경우를 제외하면 일관되게 더 낮은 communication cost를 보인다는 점을 보여준다. 또한 두 방법 모두 동시 computation 수에 대해 선형적인 wall-clock speedup을 보인다. 이러한 결과는 두 접근법 사이의 본질적인 성능 trade-off를 명확히 하며, 구조적 조건과 분포 조건에 따라 algorithm selection을 안내한다. 재현성을 위한 code도 공개한다.","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=as9uoUepox"},{"id":"2xBfuMaUiQ","en":"Intent-Driven 6G Service Orchestration: Grounded Translation, Validation, and Decomposition","ko":"의도 주도형 6G 서비스 Orchestration: Grounded Translation, Validation, and Decomposition","authors":"Jean Martins, Leonid Mokrushin, Marin Orlic, Amardeep Kumar A","abs":"<p>Intent-based automation for 6G envisions networks steered by high-level goals rather than low-level configurations. Existing LLM-based approaches translate natural language into plausible intent representations but typically omit what production deployment requires: grounding in actual service catalogs, formal validation, and cross-layer decomposition. We address this with an agentic workflow comprising three coupled reasoning layers: (i) grounding the translation in a semantic service catalog that exposes TMF-compliant service specifications; (ii) validation of the RDF intent via SHACL structural checking against the TMF Intent Ontology; and (iii) decomposition that selects a CFSS profile via constraint satisfaction over QoS capability envelopes, then covers its infrastructure requirements with RFSS profiles via weighted set cover. Across 930 benchmark runs over six GPT-4.1/5 models, the workflow achieves 97% success in structured mode and 90% on average across natural-language scenarios, with 100% correct rejection of infeasible requests. Grounding LLM context in catalog capability metadata reduces adversarial hallucinations by 26 percentage points; larger gains than scaling model size alone.</p>","absKo":"6G를 위한 intent-based automation은 네트워크를 저수준 구성(low-level configuration)이 아니라 고수준 목표에 의해 조정되는 것으로 상정한다. 기존의 LLM 기반 접근은 자연어를 그럴듯한 intent representation으로 변환하지만, 실제 배포에 필요한 것들, 즉 실제 service catalog에 대한 grounding, 형식적 검증, cross-layer decomposition은 대개 누락한다. 우리는 이를 세 단계의 결합된 reasoning layer로 이루어진 agentic workflow로 해결한다: (i) TMF-compliant service specification을 노출하는 semantic service catalog에 변환을 grounding하는 단계; (ii) TMF Intent Ontology에 대해 SHACL structural checking으로 RDF intent를 검증하는 단계; (iii) QoS capability envelope에 대한 constraint satisfaction을 통해 CFSS profile을 선택한 뒤, weighted set cover로 RFSS profile을 사용해 그 infrastructure requirement를 포괄하는 decomposition 단계. 6개의 GPT-4.1/5 model에 걸친 930회 benchmark run에서, 이 workflow는 structured mode에서 97%의 성공률을, natural-language scenario 전반에서는 평균 90%의 성공률을 달성했으며, 실행 불가능한 요청에 대해서는 100% 정확히 거부했다. LLM context를 catalog capability metadata에 grounding하면 adversarial hallucination이 26 percentage point 감소했으며, 이는 model size를 키우는 것보다 큰 향상이다.","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=2xBfuMaUiQ"},{"id":"kcev86c3WJ","en":"Against the Monolithic Wireless World Model: Why NextG Needs Composable and Agentic Intelligence","ko":"단일체 무선 world model에 맞서며: NextG에 조합 가능하고 agentic한 지능이 필요한 이유","authors":"Aladin Djuhera, Farhan Ahmed, Vlad C. Andrei, Swanand Ravindra Kadhe, Alecio Binotto, Haris Gacanin, Holger Boche","abs":"<p>AI-native 6G visions increasingly invoke wireless foundation models, large multimodal models, and wireless world models as the natural endpoint of AI-native networking, drawing an analogy to recent developments in large language models (LLMs). We argue that this analogy is structurally incomplete. The success of LLMs is based on a broad, reusable, and largely self-contained tokenized data substrate, whereas the wireless domain lacks an equivalent data foundation. Unlike text, code, or images, wireless data such as CSI tensors, IQ samples, or scheduler logs are not self-contained: their meaning is configuration-dependent, simulator-conditioned, task-disaggregated, and weakly grounded in operational feedback, all structural bottlenecks that undermine current pre- and post-training recipes. We therefore argue that monolithic models, including mixture-of-experts (MoE) and wireless world models, are not the most realistic near-term path toward deployable AI-native networks. Instead, emerging evidence points toward composable and agentic network architectures, where general reasoning models orchestrate specialized signal processing models, classical algorithms, digital twins, standards-aware retrieval, and safety checks through explicit programmable interfaces.</p>","absKo":"AI-native 6G 비전은 점점 wireless foundation model, large multimodal model, wireless world model을 AI-native networking의 자연스러운 종착점으로 상정하며, 이를 recent development in large language models(LLMs)에 비유한다. 그러나 우리는 이 비유가 구조적으로 불완전하다고 주장한다. LLM의 성공은 광범위하게 재사용 가능하고, 대체로 자기완결적인 tokenized data substrate에 기반하지만, wireless 도메인에는 이에 대응하는 data foundation이 없다. text, code, image와 달리 CSI tensor, IQ sample, scheduler log 같은 wireless data는 자기완결적이지 않다. 그 의미는 configuration-dependent이고, simulator-conditioned이며, task-disaggregated 되어 있고, operational feedback에 대해 약하게 grounded 되어 있다. 이러한 구조적 병목은 현재의 pre-training 및 post-training recipe를 약화시킨다. 따라서 우리는 MoE(mixture-of-experts)와 wireless world model을 포함한 monolithic model이 deploy 가능한 AI-native network를 향한 가장 현실적인 단기 경로가 아니라고 본다. 그 대신, emerging evidence는 composable하고 agentic한 network architecture를 가리키며, 여기서는 general reasoning model이 명시적인 programmable interface를 통해 specialized signal processing model, classical algorithm, digital twin, standards-aware retrieval, safety check를 조율한다.","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=kcev86c3WJ"},{"id":"0RnZSA6R4v","en":"Risk-Calibrated Semantic Transmission for Communication-Efficient Heterogeneous Collaborative Inference","ko":"통신 효율적 이종 협력 추론을 위한 위험 보정 의미 전송","authors":"Byeonghyeon Park, Joonhyuk Kang","abs":"<p>This paper proposes a risk-calibrated heterogeneous collaborative inference framework that deploys a lightweight CNN at the edge and a high-capacity ViT at the server. The proposed method uses Conformal Risk Control (CRC) to calibrate the edge-side acceptance threshold with a finite-sample guarantee on the risk of incorrect local acceptance, while Adaptive Prediction Sets (APS) and Grad-CAM are combined to generate class-aware saliency maps for selective patch transmission. By transmitting only semantically informative patches when server inference is required, the proposed framework reduces communication cost while preserving inference accuracy. Experimental results on ImageNet demonstrate that the proposed method achieves 81.05% Top-1 accuracy with a communication cost of 0.26, corresponding to a 74% reduction over full-image transmission.</p>","absKo":"이 논문은 edge에 경량 CNN을, server에 고용량 ViT를 배치하는 risk-calibrated heterogeneous collaborative inference framework를 제안한다. 제안 방법은 Conformal Risk Control(CRC)을 사용해 edge-side acceptance threshold를 incorrect local acceptance 위험에 대한 finite-sample guarantee와 함께 보정하며, Adaptive Prediction Sets(APS)와 Grad-CAM을 결합해 selective patch transmission을 위한 class-aware saliency map을 생성한다. server inference가 필요할 때 semantically informative한 patch만 전송함으로써, 제안 framework는 inference accuracy를 보존하면서 communication cost를 줄인다. ImageNet 실험 결과, 제안 방법은 81.05% Top-1 accuracy와 0.26의 communication cost를 달성했으며, 이는 full-image transmission 대비 74% 감소에 해당한다.","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=0RnZSA6R4v"},{"id":"QL5zUwojjK","en":"Sample-Efficient Self-Interference Cancellation for In-Band Full Duplex Radios via In-Context Learning","ko":"In-context learning을 통한 in-band full duplex 무선의 sample-efficient self-interference cancellation","authors":"Rushabha Balaji, Abhiram Kadiyala, Danijela Cabric, Suhas Diggavi","abs":"<p>Digital self-interference cancellation is a central bottleneck in realising in-band full-duplex radios for 6G. Modern cancellers can model</p><p>power-amplifier nonlinearities accurately, but their coefficients must be re-estimated from short calibration-interval pilots whenever the amplifier, front-end, or self-interference channel drifts. We recast this online calibration problem as in-context learning (ICL): a transformer</p><p>pre-trained over a distribution of amplifier operating conditions, channel, and front-end conditions predicts the interference from a few calibration-interval examples supplied as context. On a synthetic model derived from real data, the proposed method matches the analytical Bayes-optimal predictor across context lengths. With real measured PA samples passed through a simulated Rician self-interference channel and I/Q imbalance, ICL is roughly $4.4\\times$ more sample-efficient than a widely-linear alternating-least-squares baseline. On USRP~N210 full-duplex captures, ICL reaches its NMSE floor in approximately $64\\times$ fewer calibration samples than the strongest model-based baselines. When the context samples are appropriately normalized, we also show that ICL adapts zero-shot across nominally identical hardware units.</p>","absKo":"Digital self-interference cancellation은 6G에서 in-band full-duplex radio를 실현하는 데 있어 핵심 병목이다. 현대의 canceller는 power-amplifier nonlinearity를 정확하게 모델링할 수 있지만, amplifier, front-end, 또는 self-interference channel이 드리프트할 때마다 짧은 calibration-interval pilot으로부터 계수를 다시 추정해야 한다. 우리는 이 online calibration 문제를 in-context learning (ICL)로 재정식화한다. 즉, amplifier operating condition, channel, front-end condition의 분포 위에서 pre-trained된 transformer가 context로 주어진 몇 개의 calibration-interval example만으로 interference를 예측한다. 실제 데이터에서 유도한 synthetic model에서는 제안 방법이 context length 전반에 걸쳐 analytical Bayes-optimal predictor와 일치한다. 실측 PA sample을 simulated Rician self-interference channel 및 I/Q imbalance를 거치게 한 경우, ICL은 널리 쓰이는 widely-linear alternating-least-squares baseline보다 sample-efficiency가 대략 $4.4\\times$ 높다. USRP~N210 full-duplex capture에서는 ICL이 가장 강한 model-based baseline보다 약 $64\\times$ 적은 calibration sample로 NMSE floor에 도달한다. context sample을 적절히 정규화하면, 명목상 동일한 hardware unit 간에도 ICL이 zero-shot으로 적응함을 보인다.","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=QL5zUwojjK"},{"id":"88XF6IGKCj","en":"Domain Adaptation Under Wireless Network Constraints: When Does It Become Green?","ko":"무선 네트워크 제약 하의 domain adaptation: 언제 green해지는가?","authors":"Illyyne Saffar, Aurelie Boisbunon, Shruti Bothe","abs":"<p>The deployment of data-driven models in 6G wireless networks is increasingly challenged by frequent distribution shifts that degrade performance over time. Unsupervised Domain Adaptation (UDA) offers an alternative approach by adapting the trained model to a shifted domain without requiring labels. However, UDA pipelines are often more complex than single-task training due to additional modules and optimization procedures, raising a practical question: do the benefits of adaptation come at a higher energy cost, and how does this trade-off compare to retraining when labeling effort is also considered? In this work, we investigate the energy consumption of UDA and compare it to single task. We further propose a way to determine the minimum number of target domains for which UDA becomes more energy-efficient than retraining, taking into account the labeling cost. Our results aim to clarify when UDA should be preferred over classical train-from-scratch approaches from an energy and labeling-aware perspective.</p>","absKo":"6G wireless network에서 data-driven model의 배포는 시간이 지남에 따라 성능을 저하시킬 수 있는 빈번한 distribution shift로 인해 점점 더 어려워지고 있다. Unsupervised Domain Adaptation(UDA)은 label 없이 학습된 model을 shifted domain에 적응시키는 대안적 접근법을 제공한다. 그러나 UDA pipeline은 추가 모듈과 optimization procedure 때문에 single-task training보다 종종 더 복잡하며, 이에 따라 실용적인 질문이 제기된다: adaptation의 이점은 더 높은 energy cost를 수반하는가, 그리고 labeling effort까지 고려할 때 이 trade-off는 retraining과 어떻게 비교되는가? 본 연구에서는 UDA의 energy consumption을 조사하고 이를 single task와 비교한다. 또한 labeling cost를 고려하여, UDA가 retraining보다 더 energy-efficient해지는 최소 target domain 수를 결정하는 방법을 제안한다. 우리의 결과는 energy와 labeling을 고려한 관점에서 classical train-from-scratch 접근법보다 UDA를 언제 선호해야 하는지 명확히 하는 데 목적이 있다.","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=88XF6IGKCj"},{"id":"bx6bofyZo1","en":"Structured Masked Diffusion for Joint Multiuser Decoding","ko":"공동 multiuser 복호화를 위한 구조적 마스킹 확산","authors":"Taekyun Lee, Jiyoung Yun, Jeffrey Andrews, Hyeji Kim","abs":"<p>In joint multiuser decoding, a receiver recovers a set of messages from a single noisy aggregate of many simultaneous transmissions. Classical decoders rely on rule-based mechanisms such as successive interference cancellation, joint belief propagation, or list recovery, all of which become brittle or expensive as ambiguity increases.  We propose CIDER, a learned multiuser decoder with masked-diffusion refinement steps. CIDER uses demixing to prevent duplicate-row collapse and uses parity-aware propagation to provide soft guidance from the code constraints. In higher-load regimes, we further improve reliability via a lightweight quality-guided remasking step that selectively re-decodes low-confidence sequences. On commonly used error correcting codes, CIDER matches or improves on FFT-accelerated joint belief propagation-style decoding in symbol error rate while running more than $6\\times$ to over $100\\times$ faster, with the speedup widening as the blocklength grows. Code is available at https://anonymous.4open.science/r/CIDER_2026/</p>","absKo":"joint multiuser decoding에서 수신기는 여러 동시 전송의 단일 noisy aggregate로부터 메시지 집합을 복원한다. 고전적 decoder는 successive interference cancellation, joint belief propagation, list recovery와 같은 rule-based mechanism에 의존하는데, 이러한 방법은 ambiguity가 커질수록 취약해지거나 비용이 급증한다. 우리는 masked-diffusion refinement step을 사용하는 학습된 multiuser decoder CIDER를 제안한다. CIDER는 demixing을 사용해 duplicate-row collapse를 방지하고, parity-aware propagation을 사용해 code constraint로부터 soft guidance를 제공한다. 더 높은 load regime에서는, low-confidence sequence를 선택적으로 다시 디코딩하는 lightweight quality-guided remasking step으로 신뢰성을 추가 개선한다. 널리 사용되는 error-correcting code에서 CIDER는 symbol error rate 측면에서 FFT-accelerated joint belief propagation 스타일 decoding과 동등하거나 더 나은 성능을 보이면서도 6× 이상에서 100× 이상 빠르게 동작하며, blocklength가 커질수록 speedup이 더 커진다. 코드는 https://anonymous.4open.science/r/CIDER_2026/ 에서 확인할 수 있다.","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=bx6bofyZo1"},{"id":"0b5pI8olwO","en":"Learning to Offload with Low Regret under Asymmetric Misclassification Costs","ko":"비대칭 오분류 비용 하에서 낮은 regret로 오프로딩 학습","authors":"Umang Agarwal, Vinay Sutar, Sharayu Moharir","abs":"<p>We consider edge AI systems designed for binary classification via hierarchical inference(HI): a compact local model on a resource-constrained device classifies each incoming sample, and when uncertain, forwards it to a more powerful model on a remote server over a costly wireless link, a decision called offloading. The device receives a stream of periodically generated samples and must classify each one in real time, deciding online whether to act locally or offload, trading offloading cost against misclassification risk. The challenge is that neither the local model&#x27;s true accuracy at each confidence level nor the offloading cost is known in advance and must be learned from experience. We focus on the setting where the two types of misclassifications carry different costs and propose an offloading algorithm for which we prove the first $O(\\log T)$ regret guarantee for asymmetric-cost hierarchical inference. We supplement our analytical results via experiments on four real-world datasets.</p>","absKo":"우리는 hierarchical inference(HI)를 통해 binary classification을 수행하도록 설계된 edge AI 시스템을 고려한다. 자원이 제한된 기기 위의 compact local model이 들어오는 각 sample을 분류하고, 불확실할 경우 비용이 큰 wireless link를 통해 원격 server의 더 강력한 model로 전달하는데, 이를 offloading이라 부른다. 기기는 주기적으로 생성되는 sample의 stream을 받아 각 sample을 real time으로 분류해야 하며, online으로 local에서 처리할지 offload할지를 결정하면서 offloading cost와 misclassification risk를 절충한다. 문제는 각 confidence level에서 local model의 실제 정확도와 offloading cost 어느 것도 사전에 알려져 있지 않으며, 경험을 통해 학습해야 한다는 점이다. 우리는 두 종류의 misclassification이 서로 다른 cost를 갖는 설정에 초점을 맞추고, asymmetric-cost hierarchical inference에 대해 최초의 $O(\\log T)$ regret 보장을 증명하는 offloading algorithm을 제안한다. 또한 four real-world dataset에서의 실험으로 이론 결과를 보완한다.","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=0b5pI8olwO"},{"id":"3fPOt2XEaK","en":"Interpretable and Privacy-Preserving Federated Learning via Subspace Representations","ko":"Subspace Representation을 통한 해석 가능하고 프라이버시를 보장하는 Federated Learning","authors":"Jaein Lee, Jungwoo Lee","abs":"<p>Federated Learning (FL) has emerged as a vital paradigm for privacy-preserving collaborative learning. While prototype-based interpretability offers explanations in centralized settings, its extension to FL is hindered by the risk of leaking sensitive prototypical patches and the challenge of aggregating heterogeneous client concepts. We propose FedGraSP, a novel manifold-aware, subspace-based framework that aggregates class evidence on the Grassmann manifold for part-level interpretable FL. By encoding representative part-level prototypes as subspaces on the Grassmann manifold and exploiting its rotation invariance, FedGraSP achieves well-generalized collaborative learning without transmitting private raw image patches. Our framework utilizes a projection-retraction-based gradient update to maintain manifold obedience and extends naturally to personalized FL by repurposing the final layer to adapt to each user&#x27;s dataset distribution. Extensive evaluations on fine-grained classification datasets demonstrate that FedGraSP provides faithful, part-level explanations while maintaining high utility, bridging the gap between transparent reasoning and data minimization in decentralized environments.</p>","absKo":"Federated Learning (FL)은 privacy-preserving collaborative learning을 위한 중요한 paradigm으로 부상했다. prototype-based interpretability는 centralized setting에서 설명을 제공하지만, sensitive한 prototypical patch가 유출될 위험과 heterogeneous한 client concept를 집계해야 하는 어려움 때문에 이를 FL로 확장하는 것은 쉽지 않다. 우리는 part-level interpretable FL을 위해 Grassmann manifold 위에서 class evidence를 집계하는, manifold-aware subspace-based framework인 FedGraSP를 제안한다. 대표적인 part-level prototype를 Grassmann manifold 위의 subspace로 인코딩하고 그 rotation invariance를 활용함으로써, FedGraSP는 private raw image patch를 전송하지 않고도 잘 일반화되는 collaborative learning을 달성한다. 우리의 framework는 projection-retraction 기반 gradient update를 사용해 manifold obedience를 유지하며, 마지막 layer를 재활용하여 각 사용자의 dataset distribution에 적응하는 personalized FL로 자연스럽게 확장된다. fine-grained classification dataset에 대한 광범위한 평가 결과, FedGraSP는 높은 utility를 유지하면서도 faithful한 part-level 설명을 제공하여, 분산 환경에서 transparent reasoning과 data minimization 사이의 간극을 메운다.","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=3fPOt2XEaK"},{"id":"rntYcXRrq0","en":"Beyond Exact-Match: Semantic Authentication for AI-Native Wireless Systems","ko":"정확한 일치 이상: AI 네이티브 무선 시스템을 위한 의미론적 인증","authors":"Sang Wu Kim, Anders Host-Madsen","abs":"<p>AI-native NextG wireless systems increasingly exchange compressed, generated, and machine-interpretable representations whose value lies in their meaning rather than in exact message recovery. This shift creates a mismatch with conventional authentication mechanisms, which verify bit-level or message-level equality and may reject benign semantic transformations. We propose a semantic authentication</p><p>framework that accepts a recovered meaning whenever it remains within an admissible equivalence class of the intended meaning. The</p><p>equivalence classes are induced by a description-length-based semantic distance, which measures the excess coding cost incurred when an observation generated under one meaning is interpreted under another. Using this metric, we develop a set-based authentication rule with an invariant semantic hash, analyze the resulting false-rejection probability under benign perturbations, and validate the analytical results through simulation.</p>","absKo":"AI-native NextG wireless system은 점점 더 압축된, 생성된, 그리고 machine-interpretable한 representation을 교환하고 있으며, 그 가치의 중심은 정확한 message 복원이 아니라 의미에 있다. 이러한 변화는 비트 수준 또는 메시지 수준의 동일성을 검증하고 benign semantic transformation을 거부할 수 있는 기존 authentication mechanism과의 불일치를 낳는다. 우리는 회수된 의미가 의도된 의미의 허용 가능한 equivalence class 안에 남아 있는 한 이를 받아들이는 semantic authentication\\nframework를 제안한다. 이 equivalence class는 description-length-based semantic distance에 의해 유도되며, 이는 하나의 의미 아래에서 생성된 observation을 다른 의미로 해석할 때 발생하는 초과 coding cost를 측정한다. 이 metric을 사용해 우리는 invariant semantic hash를 갖는 set-based authentication rule을 개발하고, benign perturbation 하에서의 false-rejection probability를 분석하며, 시뮬레이션을 통해 분석 결과를 검증한다.","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=rntYcXRrq0"},{"id":"lr7ZmbjJgw","en":"Capacity-Aware Federated Offline Reinforcement Learning for Resource-Heterogeneous Edge Clients","ko":"자원 이질적인 edge client를 위한 용량 인식 federated offline reinforcement learning","authors":"Seungchan Yu, Kyungjae Lee, Jungchan Cho, Jungwoo Lee","abs":"<p>Federated offline reinforcement learning (FORL) is a promising abstraction for distributed edge decision making, particularly in resource-heterogeneous wireless environments with decentralized operational logs. Existing FORL methods, however, typically assume that every client can train the same full policy model, which is unrealistic when memory, compute, and energy budgets vary substantially across clients. We study FORL under client capacity heterogeneity, where high-capacity clients train a full policy model while low-capacity clients can train only masked constrained models. We propose a capacity-aware framework that combines a high-capacity warm start, aggregation-compatible masking, masked parameter aggregation, and server-side progressive distillation to transfer knowledge from an evolving full model to a constrained model that remains trainable by low-capacity clients. To isolate this algorithmic question, we evaluate Decision Transformer on standard D4RL locomotion tasks rather than domain-specific wireless simulators. Results provide preliminary evidence that low-capacity clients can be incorporated without collapsing full-model performance, while improving constrained-model performance over uniformly low-capacity federated training.</p>","absKo":"Federated offline reinforcement learning(FORL)은 분산 edge decision making을 위한 유망한 추상화이며, 특히 운영 로그가 분산된 자원 이질적 wireless environment에서 유용하다. 그러나 기존 FORL method는 보통 모든 client가 동일한 full policy model을 학습할 수 있다고 가정하는데, 이는 client마다 memory, compute, energy budget이 크게 다른 현실에서는 비현실적이다. 우리는 high-capacity client는 full policy model을 학습하고 low-capacity client는 masked constrained model만 학습할 수 있는 client capacity heterogeneity 하에서 FORL을 연구한다. 이를 위해 우리는 high-capacity warm start, aggregation-compatible masking, masked parameter aggregation, 그리고 server-side progressive distillation을 결합한 capacity-aware framework를 제안한다. 이 framework는 진화하는 full model의 지식을 low-capacity client도 학습 가능한 constrained model로 전이한다. 이 알고리즘적 질문을 분리해 보기 위해, 우리는 domain-specific wireless simulator 대신 표준 D4RL locomotion task에서 Decision Transformer를 평가한다. 결과는 low-capacity client를 도입해도 full-model performance가 붕괴하지 않으며, uniformly low-capacity federated training보다 constrained-model performance가 향상됨을 보여 주는 예비 증거를 제공한다.","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=lr7ZmbjJgw"},{"id":"tf12G6A1GT","en":"PilotWiMAE: Wireless Channel Pilots Are All You Need","ko":"PilotWiMAE: 무선 채널 파일럿만 있으면 충분하다","authors":"Berkay Guler, Giovanni Geraci, Hamid Jafarkhani","abs":"<p>Wireless channel foundation models assume access to fully observed channels, an assumption that fails in deployment. We introduce PilotWiMAE, a self-supervised framework whose encoder ingests noisy pilot observations directly and whose attention factorizes along the axis separating temporal from joint space-frequency processing, an inductive bias grounded in the physics of the problem. Pilot input shrinks the observation space by up to two orders of magnitude, while the factorized design yields more robust representations by exploiting separable channel structure and allowing a 99% pretraining mask ratio. Pilot-only processing also removes the unrealistic assumption of full-CSI availability while incurring lower latency. We pair patch-normalized reconstruction, which captures small-scale fading structure, with an auxiliary scale loss that recovers the large-scale fading features, and use an AWGN curriculum to match pilot noise at pretraining and deployment. Pretrained solely on 3.5 GHz and evaluated at 28 GHz across in-distribution and out-of-distribution settings, PilotWiMAE&#x27;s cross-frequency beam selection and channel characterization beat supervised baselines despite operating on a significantly smaller observation space.</p>","absKo":"Wireless channel foundation model은 완전히 관측된 channel에 접근할 수 있다고 가정하지만, 실제 배포에서는 이 가정이 성립하지 않는다. 우리는 PilotWiMAE를 제안한다. 이는 noisy pilot observation을 encoder가 직접 입력으로 받아들이는 self-supervised 프레임워크이며, attention은 temporal 처리와 joint space-frequency 처리를 가르는 축을 따라 factorization되도록 설계되어 문제의 물리학에 기반한 inductive bias를 반영한다. Pilot 입력은 observation space를 최대 두 자릿수 규모까지 줄이며, factorized 설계는 separable channel structure를 활용하고 99% pretraining mask ratio를 허용함으로써 더 강건한 representation을 제공한다. Pilot-only 처리는 full-CSI 가용성이라는 비현실적 가정도 제거하는 동시에 latency를 낮춘다. 우리는 작은 규모의 fading structure를 포착하는 patch-normalized reconstruction과, large-scale fading feature를 복원하는 auxiliary scale loss를 결합하고, pretraining과 deployment에서 pilot noise를 맞추기 위해 AWGN curriculum을 사용한다. 3.5 GHz에서만 사전학습하고 28 GHz에서 in-distribution 및 out-of-distribution 설정 전반에 걸쳐 평가했을 때, PilotWiMAE는 훨씬 더 작은 observation space에서 동작함에도 supervised baseline보다 cross-frequency beam selection과 channel characterization에서 더 좋은 성능을 보였다.","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=tf12G6A1GT"},{"id":"z0EsbS0uH6","en":"Value Decomposition Fails in Anti-Coordination: A Systematic MARL Comparison for Dynamic Spectrum Access in Dense 6G Networks","ko":"비협조 상황에서 값 분해는 실패한다: 밀집 6G 네트워크의 동적 스펙트럼 접근을 위한 체계적 MARL 비교","authors":"Aayam Bansal, Raghav Agarwal, Ishaan Gangwani","abs":"<p>Dynamic spectrum access (DSA) requires secondary users to select different channels to avoid mutual interference, making it a fundamentally anti-coordination problem. We present the largest systematic comparison of multi-agent reinforcement learning for DSA, evaluating fourteen methods across six paradigms: non-learning baselines (Random, Greedy, Slotted ALOHA, p-CSMA), multi-player bandit algorithms (Musical Chairs, SIC-MMAB), independent learners (IDQN, IDRQN, IPPO), and centralized-training decentralized-execution methods spanning value decomposition (VDN, QMIX, QPLEX), counterfactual credit assignment (COMA-lite), and centralized-critic policy gradient (MAPPO). In a realistic simulation with Rayleigh fading and Markov-modulated primary user activity, value decomposition methods achieve only 0.34 to 0.43 bps/Hz averaged over five seeds, dramatically underperforming even the Random baseline at 1.10 bps/Hz (95% CI: [1.096, 1.110]) in our DSA environments. This failure persists across all interventions tested: IGM-complete decomposition (QPLEX), agent-ID symmetry breaking, increased replay ratios, richer observations via PU sensing, extended training to 2.2x the original budget (52,500 steps), and the addition of an idle action, where extended training actually worsens value decomposition performance. Critically, value decomposition remains below Random even at the highest density tested (N = 50): VDN achieves 0.157, QMIX 0.164, and QPLEX 0.168 bps/Hz, compared to Random at 0.299. We show analytically that the constant PU collision rate observed across all methods (around 0.375) is consistent with reward-rational behavior rather than optimization failure: avoiding PU-active channels would concentrate agents onto fewer free channels, increasing SU congestion and reducing throughput. A counterfactual credit assignment baseline (COMA-lite) exhibits bimodal behavior across five seeds: two seeds converge to throughput matching IPPO (around 1.09), while three seeds collapse to near-zero (around 0.09), yielding a 40% success rate that highlights both the promise and current instability of counterfactual methods. Policy gradient methods (IPPO, MAPPO) emerge as the only learned methods to consistently match or surpass stochastic baselines across all densities in our DSA environments.</p>","absKo":"Dynamic spectrum access(DSA)는 secondary user가 상호 간섭을 피하기 위해 서로 다른 channel을 선택해야 하므로, 본질적으로 anti-coordination 문제이다. 우리는 DSA를 위한 multi-agent reinforcement learning의 가장 큰 체계적 비교를 제시하며, 여섯 개 패러다임에 걸쳐 14개 방법을 평가한다: non-learning baseline(Random, Greedy, Slotted ALOHA, p-CSMA), multi-player bandit algorithm(Musical Chairs, SIC-MMAB), independent learner(IDQN, IDRQN, IPPO), 그리고 value decomposition(VDN, QMIX, QPLEX), counterfactual credit assignment(COMA-lite), centralized-critic policy gradient(MAPPO)를 아우르는 centralized-training decentralized-execution 방법들이다. Rayleigh fading과 Markov-modulated primary user activity가 있는 현실적인 시뮬레이션에서, value decomposition 방법은 다섯 개 seed 평균 0.34에서 0.43 bps/Hz에 그쳐, DSA 환경에서의 Random baseline 1.10 bps/Hz(95% CI: [1.096, 1.110])에도 현저히 못 미친다. 이 실패는 우리가 시험한 모든 개입에서 지속된다: IGM-complete decomposition(QPLEX), agent-ID symmetry breaking, 더 높은 replay ratio, PU sensing을 통한 더 풍부한 observation, 원래 budget의 2.2배까지 확장한 학습(52,500 steps), 그리고 idle action 추가까지 포함되며, 이때 extended training은 오히려 value decomposition 성능을 악화시킨다. 결정적으로, value decomposition은 시험한 가장 높은 density(N = 50)에서도 여전히 Random보다 낮다: VDN은 0.157, QMIX는 0.164, QPLEX는 0.168 bps/Hz를 달성한 반면 Random은 0.299이다. 우리는 모든 방법에서 관측된 일정한 PU collision rate(약 0.375)가 최적화 실패가 아니라 reward-rational behavior와 일치함을 분석적으로 보인다: PU가 활성화된 channel을 피하면 agent가 더 적은 free channel로 몰리게 되어 SU congestion이 증가하고 throughput이 감소하기 때문이다. counterfactual credit assignment baseline(COMA-lite)은 다섯 개 seed에서 이중봉(bimodal) 거동을 보인다: 두 seed는 IPPO와 맞먹는 throughput(약 1.09)으로 수렴하는 반면, 세 seed는 거의 0(약 0.09)으로 붕괴하여 40%의 성공률을 나타내며, 이는 counterfactual method의 가능성과 현재의 불안정성을 동시에 부각한다. Policy gradient 방법(IPPO, MAPPO)은 우리 DSA 환경의 모든 density에서 일관되게 stochastic baseline과 동등하거나 이를 능가하는 유일한 학습 기반 방법으로 나타난다.","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=z0EsbS0uH6"},{"id":"LgeZWriDdT","en":"Inductive Latent Context Persistence: Closing the Post-Handover Cold Start in 6G Radio Access Networks","ko":"유도적 잠재 컨텍스트 지속성: 6G 무선 접속망에서 인계 후 콜드 스타트 해소","authors":"Anubhab Banerjee, Daniyal Amir Awan","abs":"<p>In modern radio access networks (RANs) rulebased handover (HO) decisions (e.g., A3/A5) depend on user equipment (UE) measurements only, resulting in different HO decisons for UEs who are in the same location. To overcome it, graph neural networks (GNNs) based methods have been proposed to improve HO key performance indicators (KPIs) using more information than just the measurements. However, existing recurrent or graph-based methods discard the per- UE recurrent state at HO and reinitialize it at the target next-generation NodeB (gNB) – losing useful measurement and mobility history as part of the overall context, forcing the target-side model to rebuild the state from post-HO measurements only. We address this post-HO cold start problem with Inductive Latent Context Persistence (ILCP), a learned latent synchronization mechanism that compresses the source-side per- UE recurrent state, transports it over the standard 3GPP Xn interface (Xn) as a 128-byte payload, and adapts it to the target gNB state space at HO. We model the RAN as a dynamic heterogeneous graph, allowing the model to treat UE nodes, gNB nodes, measurement edges, and Xn neighbor edges separately. On the Vienna 4G/5G drive-test, ILCP eliminates ping-pong HOs in the test split with 0.0% compared with 6.5% for the otherwise identical but no-transfer baseline and 22.6% for a Transformer baseline. It also achieves a +5.1 pp average post-HO accuracy gain, with a peak gain of +13.3 pp, over the no-transfer baseline in the 50–250 ms post-HO window. On a single NVIDIA GTX 1080 (8 GB), ILCP runs endto- end at 7.7 ms p99 per handover decision. Under measurement perturbations including shadow fading, non-line-of-sight (NLOS) blockage, and synchronization signal block (SSB)-burst sparsity, robustly trained ILCP keeps handover failure (HOF) in the 10–13% and exposes sub optimality of relying only on measurements. In the same fixed-reference-label setting, the 3GPP A3/A5 rule which relies only on measurements increases from 1.1% HOF on the unperturbed trace to 57– 65% under perturbed measurements.</p>","absKo":"현대 radio access network(RAN)에서 rule-based handover(HO) 결정(예: A3/A5)은 user equipment(UE) 측정값에만 의존하므로, 같은 위치에 있는 UE들 사이에서도 서로 다른 HO 결정이 발생한다. 이를 극복하기 위해, 측정값보다 더 많은 정보를 활용하여 HO key performance indicator(KPI)를 개선하는 graph neural network(GNN) 기반 방법들이 제안되어 왔다. 그러나 기존의 recurrent 또는 graph-based 방법은 HO 시 UE의 per-UE recurrent state를 버리고 target next-generation NodeB(gNB)에서 이를 재초기화한다. 그 결과, 전체 context의 일부인 유용한 측정 및 mobility history를 잃게 되고, target-side model은 HO 이후의 측정값만으로 state를 다시 구성해야 한다. 우리는 이 post-HO cold start 문제를 Inductive Latent Context Persistence(ILCP)로 해결한다. ILCP는 source-side per-UE recurrent state를 압축하고, 이를 표준 3GPP Xn interface(Xn)를 통해 128-byte payload로 전송하며, HO 시 target gNB state space에 맞게 적응시키는 learned latent synchronization mechanism이다. 우리는 RAN을 dynamic heterogeneous graph로 모델링하여, model이 UE node, gNB node, measurement edge, Xn neighbor edge를 별도로 다루도록 한다. Vienna 4G/5G drive-test에서 ILCP는 test split에서 ping-pong HO를 0.0%로 제거했으며, 이는 동일하지만 transfer가 없는 baseline의 6.5%, Transformer baseline의 22.6%와 대비된다. 또한 50–250 ms post-HO window에서 no-transfer baseline 대비 평균 post-HO accuracy를 +5.1 pp 향상시키고, 최대 +13.3 pp의 향상을 보였다. 단일 NVIDIA GTX 1080(8 GB)에서 ILCP는 handover decision당 end-to-end 7.7 ms p99로 동작한다. shadow fading, non-line-of-sight(NLOS) blockage, synchronization signal block(SSB)-burst sparsity를 포함한 measurement perturbation 하에서 robust하게 학습된 ILCP는 handover failure(HOF)를 10–13% 수준으로 유지하며, 측정값에만 의존하는 것의 suboptimality를 드러낸다. 같은 fixed-reference-label setting에서, 측정값에만 의존하는 3GPP A3/A5 rule은 perturbation이 없는 trace에서 1.1% HOF이던 것이 perturb된 measurement 하에서는 57–65%로 증가한다.","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=LgeZWriDdT"},{"id":"0NclSTqiWl","en":"Normalization-Free Knowledge Distillation for Variable-Bit CSI Feedback in Massive MIMO","ko":"Massive MIMO에서 가변 비트 CSI 피드백을 위한 정규화 없는 지식 증류","authors":"Eunju Seo, WooJun Kim, Dongjin Ji","abs":"<p>Efficient Channel State Information (CSI) feedback is critical for beamforming in Frequency Division Duplexing (FDD) Massive MIMO, yet variable-bit deep learning schemes suffer from trailing-bit information loss under constrained training budgets~\\citep{ji2024concrete}. While Knowledge Distillation (KD) is a natural remedy, we identify a previously overlooked problem: standard Z-score normalization applied during KD destroys the physical scale information embedded in wireless channel tensors, degrading reconstruction quality across variable feedback lengths. We propose Normalization-Free Knowledge Distillation (NF-KD), a training framework that preserves physical scale by applying Kullback--Leibler Divergence (KLD) directly to raw, temperature-scaled tensors without any normalization step. Experiments on the DeepMIMO dataset show that NF-KD achieves $-12.87$\\,dB Normalized Mean Squared Error (NMSE) at 256 bits (vs.\\ $-11.98$\\,dB baseline), consistent cosine similarity gains across all feedback lengths, and a $0.056$\\,dB reduction in beamforming gain loss that translates to $+0.019$\\,bps/Hz spectral efficiency under Zero-Forcing (ZF) precoding at $20$\\,dB Signal-to-Noise Ratio (SNR)---all within a 500-epoch training budget. Ablation confirms that normalization is the critical failure factor.</p>","absKo":"효율적인 Channel State Information(CSI) 피드백은 Frequency Division Duplexing(FDD) Massive MIMO에서 beamforming에 핵심적이지만, 가변 비트 deep learning 방식은 제한된 training budget 하에서 trailing-bit 정보 손실을 겪는다~\\citep{ji2024concrete}. Knowledge Distillation(KD)은 자연스러운 해결책이지만, 우리는 이전에 간과된 문제를 식별한다. KD 동안 적용되는 표준 Z-score normalization이 무선 채널 tensor에 내재된 물리적 scale 정보를 파괴하여, 가변 feedback length 전반의 reconstruction quality를 저하시킨다는 점이다. 우리는 Normalization-Free Knowledge Distillation(NF-KD)을 제안한다. 이는 어떤 normalization 단계도 거치지 않고 raw temperature-scaled tensor에 직접 Kullback--Leibler Divergence(KLD)를 적용하여 물리적 scale을 보존하는 training framework이다. DeepMIMO dataset 실험에서 NF-KD는 256 bits에서 $-12.87$\\,dB Normalized Mean Squared Error(NMSE)를 달성했으며(기본선 $-11.98$\\,dB 대비), 모든 feedback length에서 일관된 cosine similarity 향상을 보였고, beamforming gain loss를 $0.056$\\,dB 줄여 Zero-Forcing(ZF) precoding과 $20$\\,dB Signal-to-Noise Ratio(SNR) 조건에서 $+0.019$\\,bps/Hz spectral efficiency 향상으로 이어졌다. 이 모든 결과는 500-epoch training budget 내에서 달성되었다. Ablation은 normalization이 핵심적인 failure factor임을 확인한다.","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=0NclSTqiWl"},{"id":"zMogeI2Sbk","en":"Toward Reliable Intrusion Monitoring for O-RAN Based Networks with Conformal False Alarm Control","ko":"conformal false alarm control을 이용한 O-RAN 기반 네트워크의 신뢰할 수 있는 침입 모니터링을 향하여","authors":"Joohong Rheey, Hyunggon Park","abs":"<p>Autoencoder-based intrusion detectors provide a practical option for Open Radio Access Network (O-RAN) environments because they can be trained from benign traffic and deployed as monitoring components, such as eXtended Applications. However, alarm thresholds of the intrusion detectors are typically determined by heuristic rules, which makes them difficult to integrate into confidence-gated closed-loop management. In this type of management, uncontrolled false alarms may trigger disruptive mitigation actions. In this paper, we propose a covariance-aware conformal detector for unsupervised intrusion detection with a false alarm rate (FAR) constraint. The method uses a Mahalanobis distance in the reconstruction error space of the autoencoder as the nonconformity score and calibrates the threshold by split conformal prediction. Under exchangeability between the benign calibration samples and future benign test samples, the proposed detector controls the FAR within a user-specified budget. For 5th Generation traffic, the proposed score increases the detection rate compared to the conformal baseline at the same target FAR. The quadratic score also decomposes exactly into feature-wise diagnostic terms, providing low-cost per-alarm triage without post-hoc explanation models. The online detector operates with microsecond-scale latency, which enables deployment to Near-Real-Time RAN Intelligent Controller.</p>","absKo":"Autoencoder 기반 intrusion detector는 Open Radio Access Network (O-RAN) 환경에서 실용적인 선택지를 제공한다. benign traffic만으로 학습할 수 있고 eXtended Applications와 같은 monitoring component로 배포할 수 있기 때문이다. 그러나 intrusion detector의 alarm threshold는 일반적으로 heuristic rule로 결정되며, 이로 인해 confidence-gated closed-loop management에 통합하기 어렵다. 이러한 유형의 관리에서는 통제되지 않은 false alarm이 disruptive mitigation action을 유발할 수 있다. 본 논문에서는 false alarm rate (FAR) 제약이 있는 unsupervised intrusion detection을 위한 covariance-aware conformal detector를 제안한다. 이 방법은 autoencoder의 reconstruction error space에서 Mahalanobis distance를 nonconformity score로 사용하고, split conformal prediction으로 threshold를 보정한다. benign calibration sample과 미래의 benign test sample 사이에 exchangeability가 성립하면, 제안하는 detector는 사용자가 지정한 budget 내에서 FAR을 제어한다. 5th Generation traffic에 대해, 제안한 score는 동일한 target FAR에서 conformal baseline보다 detection rate를 높인다. 또한 이 quadratic score는 feature-wise diagnostic term으로 정확히 분해되므로, post-hoc explanation model 없이도 저비용 per-alarm triage를 제공한다. 온라인 detector는 microsecond-scale latency로 동작하여 Near-Real-Time RAN Intelligent Controller에 배포할 수 있다.","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=zMogeI2Sbk"},{"id":"32sPk5wWVj","en":"Video Generation Empowered Long-Term Radio Map Prediction in UAV-Assisted Communication","ko":"UAV 지원 통신에서 Video Generation을 활용한 장기 Radio Map 예측","authors":"Lin Zhu, Weifeng Zhu, Shuowen Zhang, Liang Liu","abs":"<p>Radio maps provide rich information about the radio landscape that is useful to a myriad of wireless communication and sensing applications. In contrast to the scenario with fixed-position transmitters, the transmitter in the unmanned aerial vehicle (UAV)-assisted communication scenario can move along a predefined trajectory, resulting in a continuously evolving \\emph{long-term radio map}. To address this long-term radio map prediction problem, existing deep learning-based methods that follow the image-to-image translation approach suffer from significant complexity and limited accuracy due to their independent frame-by-frame construction method, which neglects the temporal correlation of radio characteristics. In this work, we formulate the long-term radio map prediction problem in the UAV-assisted communication system as a \\emph{conditioned video generation} task. In particular, we propose a \\emph{lightweight} model that encodes the static environment only once, conditions radio map prediction on both the environment and the UAV trajectory, and refines the generated sequence in the temporal domain by exploiting double-sided dependencies. Experiments on a large-scale simulated dataset demonstrate that the proposed method consistently improves prediction accuracy and temporal consistency while reducing computational redundancy compared with both static baselines and sequential baselines. The source code is available at \\href{https://github.com/LINZHU-PolyU/DynamicRadioMap}{GitHub repository}.</p>","absKo":"Radio map은 무선 환경에 대한 풍부한 정보를 제공하며, 이는 다양한 wireless communication 및 sensing 응용에서 유용하다. 위치가 고정된 transmitter와 달리, unmanned aerial vehicle(UAV)-assisted communication 시나리오의 transmitter는 미리 정의된 trajectory를 따라 이동할 수 있어, 시간이 지남에 따라 지속적으로 진화하는 \\emph{long-term radio map}이 형성된다. 이 long-term radio map 예측 문제를 다루기 위해, 기존의 image-to-image translation 접근을 따르는 deep learning 기반 방법들은 radio 특성의 시간적 상관관계를 무시하는 독립적인 frame-by-frame 구성 방식 때문에 상당한 복잡도와 제한된 정확도 문제를 보인다. 본 연구에서는 UAV-assisted communication system에서의 long-term radio map 예측 문제를 \\emph{conditioned video generation} 작업으로 정식화한다. 특히, 정적 환경을 한 번만 인코딩하고, radio map 예측을 환경과 UAV trajectory 모두에 조건화하며, 양방향 의존성을 활용해 생성된 시퀀스를 시간적 차원에서 정제하는 \\emph{lightweight} 모델을 제안한다. 대규모 시뮬레이션 데이터셋에서 수행한 실험은, 제안 방법이 static baseline과 sequential baseline 모두에 비해 계산 중복을 줄이면서 예측 정확도와 시간적 일관성을 일관되게 향상시킴을 보여준다. 소스 코드는 \\href{https://github.com/LINZHU-PolyU/DynamicRadioMap}{GitHub repository}에서 उपलब्ध하다.","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=32sPk5wWVj"},{"id":"JvlFJCSCVZ","en":"Deep Reinforcement Learning-based Multi-Target Tracking and Association in Cooperative Millimeter-Wave ISAC Systems","ko":"협력적 밀리미터파 ISAC 시스템에서의 다중 표적 추적과 연계를 위한 Deep Reinforcement Learning 기반 방법","authors":"Tongkai LI, Weifeng Zhu, Shuowen Zhang, Jiannong Cao, Shuguang Cui, Liang Liu","abs":"<p>This paper investigates the multi-target tracking (MTT) problem in a cooperative millimeter-wave (mmWave) integrated sensing and communication (ISAC) system, where distributed base stations (BSs) emit directional beams to probe the states of associated targets. Owing to the complicated environment and target mobilities, the target-BS associations need to be dynamically adjusted to facilitate stable MTT performance during the tracking interval. In this work, we propose a unified deep reinforcement learning (DRL)-based framework to perform joint target state estimation, target-BS association adjustment, and beam prediction tasks. Specifically, a dynamic graph neural network (DGNN) is first developed to capture the spatio-temporal features among targets and perform target state estimation. In particular, an advantage actor-critic (A2C)-based controller is then proposed for flexible target-BS association adjustment and beam prediction under a novel auto-regressive policy, which ensures that the target‑BS association constraints can be strictly satisfied. Numerical results demonstrate that the proposed scheme can adaptively update associations in response to target mobility, thereby significantly reducing the tracking error.</p>","absKo":"본 논문은 협력적 millimeter-wave(mmWave) integrated sensing and communication(ISAC) 시스템에서의 multi-target tracking(MTT) 문제를 다룬다. 이 시스템에서는 분산 base station(BS)들이 방향성 빔을 방출하여 연결된 target의 상태를 탐지한다. 복잡한 환경과 target의 이동성 때문에, 추적 구간 동안 안정적인 MTT 성능을 유지하기 위해 target-BS association을 동적으로 조정할 필요가 있다. 본 연구에서는 target 상태 추정, target-BS association 조정, beam prediction task를 공동으로 수행하기 위한 통합 deep reinforcement learning(DRL) 기반 프레임워크를 제안한다. 구체적으로, 먼저 dynamic graph neural network(DGNN)를 개발하여 target 간 spatio-temporal feature를 포착하고 target 상태를 추정한다. 이어서, 새로운 auto-regressive policy 하에서 유연한 target-BS association 조정과 beam prediction을 위해 advantage actor-critic(A2C) 기반 controller를 제안하며, 이를 통해 target-BS association 제약을 엄격하게 만족시킬 수 있도록 한다. 수치 결과는 제안 방식이 target mobility에 따라 association을 적응적으로 갱신하여 tracking error를 크게 줄일 수 있음을 보여준다.","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=JvlFJCSCVZ"},{"id":"KiCdcoQMoS","en":"PAW: Parallel-Wavelet Attention for Lightweight Asymmetric Semantic Image Communication in 6G Space Networks","ko":"PAW: 6G 우주 네트워크에서 경량 비대칭 의미 이미지 통신을 위한 Parallel-Wavelet Attention","authors":"Ziyang MENG, Yuheng Zhang, Lu Lu, Jianhua He, Yongsheng Gong","abs":"<p>An important challenge in semantic communication for 6G space networks is achieving reliable image reconstruction under low-SNR conditions with constrained onboard resources. Existing Swin-based schemes rely on symmetric transceivers and spatial-only attention, which are not well suited to satellite--cloud systems. To address these issues, we propose PAW, a Parallel-Wavelet Attention-based asymmetric architecture for semantic image communication. PAW integrates discrete wavelet transform (DWT) to enable high-fidelity channel and spatial attention through parallel frequency-aware recalibration paths. Lightweight MBConv and DSConv modules are further employed to reduce encoder-side computational complexity. Experiments show that PAW reduces encoder-side GPU runtime by up to 3.5 times compared to Swin-based baselines, while maintaining competitive reconstruction performance. These results suggest that joint channel &amp; spatial attention is an effective design for future resource-constrained 6G space semantic communications.</p>","absKo":"6G space network의 semantic communication에서 중요한 과제는 온보드 자원이 제한된 상태에서 low-SNR 조건 아래 신뢰할 수 있는 image reconstruction을 달성하는 것이다. 기존 Swin 기반 scheme은 symmetric transceiver와 spatial-only attention에 의존하는데, 이는 satellite--cloud system에 적합하지 않다. 이러한 문제를 해결하기 위해 우리는 semantic image communication을 위한 Parallel-Wavelet Attention 기반 asymmetric architecture인 PAW를 제안한다. PAW는 discrete wavelet transform (DWT)을 통합하여 parallel frequency-aware recalibration path를 통해 고충실도 channel 및 spatial attention을 가능하게 한다. 또한 lightweight MBConv와 DSConv module을 사용하여 encoder-side computational complexity를 낮춘다. 실험 결과, PAW는 Swin 기반 baseline과 비교해 encoder-side GPU runtime을 최대 3.5배 줄이면서도 경쟁력 있는 reconstruction 성능을 유지한다. 이러한 결과는 joint channel & spatial attention이 향후 자원 제약이 큰 6G space semantic communication을 위한 효과적인 설계임을 시사한다.","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=KiCdcoQMoS"},{"id":"1XgS8gKIQ6","en":"Efficient Graph Attention-based Learning for Traffic Prediction and Uncertainty-Aware Anomaly Detection in AI-driven O-RAN","ko":"AI 기반 O-RAN에서 교통 예측과 불확실성 인지 이상 탐지를 위한 효율적 Graph Attention 기반 학습","authors":"Tzu-Herng Wang, Lan-Huong Nguyen, Ren-Hung Hwang, Van-Linh Nguyen","abs":"<p>Traffic load prediction to enable proactive congestion management and resource optimization  in Open Radio Access Networks (O-RAN) is challenging, given exhibit distinct temporal patterns, dynamic ranges, and burst behaviors in multiple service slices. To address this challenge, we propose a novelly efficient traffic prediction architecture that processes sixteen radio-level features through three parallel branches: a per-feature shared BiLSTM for temporal dynamics, a Graph Attention Network (GAT) over a feature-as-node graph for cross-feature dependencies, and a dual Transformer over magnitude and phase spectra from the input window. The branch outputs are fused per node, mean-pooled across nodes, and trained per network service slice using a single-step regression objective on granted physical resource blocks. We apply mean squared error for the smoother eMBB slice and show that pure Huber loss is more effective for the burstier mMTC and uRLLC slices than both mean squared error and upper-tail weighted mean squared error. A post-hoc Chebyshev test calibrated on validation residuals converts predictions into a slice-aware anomaly flag without labeled anomalies. On the Colosseum O-RAN dataset, the model achieves promising performance, $R^2 = 0.9011$ on eMBB, $R^2 = 0.3002$ on mMTC, and $R^2 = 0.6624$ on uRLLC, outperforming the existing studies with Chebyshev flag rates below $3.5\\%$ across all slices.</p>","absKo":"Open Radio Access Network(O-RAN)에서 proactive congestion management와 resource optimization을 가능하게 하기 위한 traffic load prediction은 여러 service slice에서 서로 다른 temporal pattern, dynamic range, burst behavior를 보이기 때문에 어렵다. 이러한 문제를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 16개의 radio-level feature를 세 개의 parallel branch로 처리하는 새롭고 효율적인 traffic prediction architecture를 제안한다. 하나는 temporal dynamics를 위한 feature별 shared BiLSTM, 하나는 cross-feature dependency를 위한 feature-as-node graph 위의 Graph Attention Network(GAT), 그리고 하나는 입력 window의 magnitude와 phase spectrum을 위한 dual Transformer이다. branch output은 node별로 fusion되고, node 전반에 대해 mean pooling되며, granted physical resource block에 대한 single-step regression objective로 network service slice별로 학습된다. 우리는 더 매끄러운 eMBB slice에는 mean squared error를 적용하고, 더 bursty한 mMTC와 uRLLC slice에는 mean squared error 및 upper-tail weighted mean squared error보다 pure Huber loss가 더 효과적임을 보인다. validation residual로 보정한 post-hoc Chebyshev test는 label이 없는 anomaly를 slice-aware anomaly flag로 변환한다. Colosseum O-RAN dataset에서 이 모델은 유망한 성능을 보였으며, eMBB에서 $R^2 = 0.9011$, mMTC에서 $R^2 = 0.3002$, uRLLC에서 $R^2 = 0.6624$를 달성해 기존 연구를 능가했고, 모든 slice에서 Chebyshev flag rate는 $3.5\\%$ 미만이었다.","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=1XgS8gKIQ6"},{"id":"WUOslxuWQb","en":"Self-Explaining Reinforcement Learning for Mobile Network Resource Allocation","ko":"모바일 네트워크 자원 할당을 위한 자기설명형 강화학습","authors":"Konrad Nowosadko, Franco Ruggeri, Ahmad Terra","abs":"<p>Deep reinforcement learning (DRL) methods, though powerful, often lack transparency, which limits their adoption in critical domains. We apply Self-Explaining Neural Networks (SENNs) to RL by parametrizing the policy of a PPO agent with a SENN, producing intrinsic local explanations, and propose a method for aggregating them into global explanations. We evaluate our approach on a mobile network resource allocation problem, our approach performs within a small margin of the state-of-the-art deep learning method and significantly outperforms the best deployed heuristic, while the extracted global explanations correlate strongly with DeepLift and InputXGradient, making SENNs a promising candidate for high-stakes RL.</p>","absKo":"Deep reinforcement learning(DRL) 방법은 강력하지만, 종종 투명성이 부족하여 핵심 영역에서의 채택을 제한한다. 우리는 Self-Explaining Neural Networks(SENNs)를 RL에 적용하여 PPO agent의 policy를 SENN으로 parameterize함으로써 내재적인 local explanation을 생성하고, 이를 global explanation으로 집계하는 방법을 제안한다. 우리는 모바일 네트워크 자원 할당 문제에서 이 접근법을 평가했으며, 우리의 방법은 최신 deep learning 방법과의 격차가 작고 가장 우수한 배포 heuristic을 유의하게 능가하는 성능을 보였다. 또한 추출된 global explanation은 DeepLift 및 InputXGradient와 강하게 상관되어, SENNs가 고위험 RL을 위한 유망한 후보임을 보여준다.","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=WUOslxuWQb"},{"id":"IO4dkCEfwR","en":"Beyond Type-II: Site-Specific Subspace Inference for Efficient CSI Feedback","ko":"Type-II를 넘어: 효율적 CSI feedback을 위한 site-specific subspace 추론","authors":"Cheng-Jie Zhao, Zhaolin Wang, Zongyao Zhao, Yuanwei Liu","abs":"<p>We propose a site-specific Type-II feedback design for downlink limited-feedback beamforming. The paper first formulates an effective-rate objective that couples channel-state information (CSI) probing, user equipment (UE)-side compression, base station (BS)-side reconstruction, and online overhead. Guided by this objective, the BS uses a low-overhead synchronization signal block (SSB) reference signal received power (RSRP) fingerprint and a learned site-specific propagation prior to infer a UE-dependent dominant beam subspace before explicit CSI acquisition. The UE then estimates and reports only the effective channel coefficients in this subspace, avoiding full-dimensional online subspace search while retaining a Type-II-style multi-beam representation. We analyze the resulting subspace-capture behavior and jointly optimize the probing codebook and subspace inference network for channel-energy preservation. Experiments show Type-II-comparable capture quality with lower online overhead and UE-side complexity, leading to higher effective spectral efficiency.</p>","absKo":"우리는 downlink limited-feedback beamforming을 위한 site-specific Type-II feedback design을 제안한다. 이 논문은 먼저 channel-state information(CSI) probing, user equipment(UE) 측 compression, base station(BS) 측 reconstruction, 그리고 online overhead를 결합한 effective-rate objective를 정식화한다. 이 objective에 따라 BS는 낮은 overhead의 synchronization signal block(SSB) reference signal received power(RSRP) fingerprint와 학습된 site-specific propagation prior를 사용해 explicit CSI acquisition 이전에 UE 의존적인 dominant beam subspace를 추론한다. 그런 다음 UE는 이 subspace에서의 effective channel coefficient만 추정해 보고함으로써, full-dimensional online subspace search를 피하면서도 Type-II 스타일의 multi-beam representation은 유지한다. 우리는 이로 인해 형성되는 subspace-capture behavior를 분석하고, channel-energy preservation을 위해 probing codebook과 subspace inference network를 공동 최적화한다. 실험 결과는 Type-II와 견줄 만한 capture quality를 더 낮은 online overhead와 UE 측 복잡도로 달성하며, 그 결과 더 높은 effective spectral efficiency를 얻음을 보인다.","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=IO4dkCEfwR"},{"id":"eqwHeQVlzx","en":"Distribution-Free Adaptive Modulation and Coding via Online Conformal Inference under Non-Stationary Fading","ko":"비정상 페이딩에서 온라인 conformal inference를 이용한 분포 무가정 적응 변조 및 부호화","authors":"Soham Batra, Siddharth Karuturi, Kaustubh S. Bukkapatnam, Laksh Patel, Tanush Ajay Shastry, Matthew Park","abs":"<p>Machine learning--based adaptive modulation and coding (ML-AMC) has demonstrated strong empirical performance for next-generation wireless systems, yet existing approaches provide no formal guarantees on block error rate (BLER) coverage under the non-stationary fading conditions ubiquitous in 5G-NR and 6G deployments. We propose Conformal-AMC, a principled framework that wraps any pre-trained MCS classifier with online adaptive conformal inference (ACI) to produce prediction sets with finite-sample, distribution-free miscoverage guarantees. The central theoretical contribution is a tight bound on time-averaged miscoverage that decomposes into an adaptation-noise term, a non-stationarity penalty governed by the channel Markov chain&#x27;s mixing time $\\tau_{\\text{mix}}$, and a total-variation drift $V_T$; this decomposition yields a closed-form, Doppler-adaptive learning rate $\\eta_{\\text{Jakes}}^*$ computable entirely from pilot-estimated channel statistics, requiring no labeled data or manual tuning. We further establish a two-sided coverage--throughput tradeoff (Theorem 4.4) and prove that antenna diversity monotonically tightens the guarantee (Theorem 4.5). Experiments under 3GPP TDL channel models at UE speeds of 3--500~km/h show that Conformal-AMC tracks the target miscoverage level $\\alpha = 0.10$ to within $\\pm 0.012$ across all speed transitions while achieving a singleton rate of 82.4\\%---exceeding the 77.1\\% of Split CP and 75.3\\% of OLLA at the same coverage level---with all pairwise improvements over baselines significant at $p &lt; 0.001$.</p>","absKo":"Machine learning 기반 adaptive modulation and coding(ML-AMC)은 차세대 무선 시스템에서 강한 실증 성능을 보여 왔지만, 기존 접근법은 5G-NR과 6G 배치 전반에서 흔한 비정상적 fading 조건 하에서 block error rate(BLER) coverage에 대한 형식적 보장을 제공하지 못한다. 우리는 사전 학습된 어떤 MCS 분류기에도 online adaptive conformal inference(ACI)를 감싸 넣어 finite-sample, distribution-free miscoverage 보장을 갖는 prediction set을 생성하는 원리적인 프레임워크인 Conformal-AMC를 제안한다. 핵심 이론 기여는 adaptation-noise 항, 채널 Markov chain의 mixing time $\\tau_{\\text{mix}}$에 의해 지배되는 non-stationarity 페널티, 그리고 total-variation drift $V_T$로 분해되는 time-averaged miscoverage에 대한 타이트한 bound이다. 이 분해는 pilot으로 추정한 채널 통계만으로 전부 계산 가능한 closed-form의 Doppler-adaptive learning rate $\\eta_{\\text{Jakes}}^*$를 도출하며, labeled data나 수동 tuning을 필요로 하지 않는다. 우리는 또한 양방향 coverage--throughput tradeoff(Theorem 4.4)를 확립하고 antenna diversity가 보장을 단조롭게 더 타이트하게 만든다는 것(Theorem 4.5)을 증명한다. UE 속도 3--500~km/h의 3GPP TDL 채널 모델에서 수행한 실험은 Conformal-AMC가 모든 속도 전이에서 목표 miscoverage 수준 $\\alpha = 0.10$을 $\\pm 0.012$ 이내로 추적하면서 singleton rate 82.4\\%를 달성함을 보여 주었다. 이는 동일한 coverage 수준에서 Split CP의 77.1\\%와 OLLA의 75.3\\%를 상회하며, baseline 대비 모든 pairwise 개선은 $p < 0.001$에서 유의했다.","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=eqwHeQVlzx"},{"id":"M4xtV1weHZ","en":"Conformal Semantic Communication: Distribution-Free Task-Level Coverage Guarantees for Goal-Oriented Transmission Under Channel Shift","ko":"Conformal Semantic Communication: 채널 시프트 하의 목표 지향 전송을 위한 분포 무관 task-level coverage 보장","authors":"Soham Batra, Siddharth Karuturi, Kaustubh S. Bukkapatnam, Laksh Patel, Tanush Ajay Shastry, Matthew Park","abs":"<p>Semantic (task-oriented) communication systems compress and transmit only the information required by a downstream AI task, promising dramatic bandwidth savings for 6G and beyond. However, existing systems provide no formal guarantees on task performance under channel uncertainty: when the fading distribution at test time differs from that seen during calibration, task error rates can be severely miscalibrated. We introduce Weighted Conformal Semantic Communication (WCSC), the first framework that couples goal-oriented transmission with distribution-free, finite-sample coverage guarantees robust to channel distribution shift. Our central theoretical contributions are: (i) a formal characterization of coverage failure as a function of total-variation distance between calibration and deployment channel distributions; (ii) a weighted conformal algorithm with exact finite-sample coverage using importance-reweighted nonconformity scores derived from channel state information; (iii) a finite-sample bound showing $\\mathcal{O}(n^{-1/2})$ calibration sample complexity with explicit dependence on weight estimation error and effective sample size; (iv) a fundamental information-theoretic lower bound on semantic transmission rate as a function of target miscoverage, identifying a critical SNR below which the coverage target is information-theoretically impossible; and (v) an optimality characterization showing that information bottleneck-trained encoders are provably optimal for this coverage-constrained problem. Experiments on CIFAR-10 and ModelNet40 across Rayleigh, UMa, and Gauss--Markov channel models confirm the theory and demonstrate that WCSC maintains calibrated coverage where all baselines fail.</p>","absKo":"Semantic(task-oriented) communication system은 하위 AI task에 필요한 정보만 압축하고 전송함으로써 6G 및 그 이후 세대에서 극적인 대역폭 절감을 약속한다. 그러나 기존 system은 channel uncertainty 하에서의 task 성능에 대한 형식적 보장을 제공하지 못한다. 즉, calibration 시점에 관측된 fading distribution과 test time의 분포가 다를 때 task error rate는 심각하게 miscalibrated될 수 있다. 우리는 channel distribution shift에 대해 견고한 distribution-free, finite-sample coverage guarantee를 결합한 최초의 framework인 Weighted Conformal Semantic Communication(WCSC)을 소개한다. 우리의 핵심 이론적 기여는 다음과 같다: (i) calibration과 deployment channel distribution 사이의 total-variation distance의 함수로서 coverage failure를 형식적으로 특성화; (ii) channel state information으로부터 도출된 importance-reweighted nonconformity score를 사용하는 정확한 finite-sample coverage를 갖는 weighted conformal algorithm; (iii) weight estimation error와 effective sample size에 대한 명시적 의존성을 포함하여 $\\mathcal{O}(n^{-1/2})$의 calibration sample complexity를 보이는 finite-sample bound; (iv) target miscoverage의 함수로서 semantic transmission rate에 대한 근본적인 information-theoretic lower bound로, 해당 coverage target이 정보이론적으로 불가능해지는 critical SNR을 식별; (v) information bottleneck으로 학습된 encoder가 이 coverage-constrained problem에 대해 이론적으로 최적임을 보이는 optimality characterization이다. CIFAR-10과 ModelNet40에서 Rayleigh, UMa, Gauss--Markov channel model 전반에 걸친 실험은 이 이론을 확인하고, WCSC가 모든 baseline이 실패하는 곳에서도 calibrated coverage를 유지함을 보여준다.","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=M4xtV1weHZ"},{"id":"gxwfDntIz5","en":"MambaCSP: Hybrid-Attention State Space Models for Hardware-Efficient Channel State Prediction","ko":"MambaCSP: hardware-efficient channel state prediction을 위한 hybrid-attention state space model","authors":"Aladin Djuhera, Haris Gacanin, Holger Boche","abs":"<p>Recent works have demonstrated that attention-based transformer and large language model (LLM) architectures can achieve strong channel state prediction (CSP) performance by capturing long-range temporal dependencies across channel state information (CSI) sequences. However, these models suffer from quadratic scaling in sequence length, leading to substantial computational cost, memory consumption, and inference latency, which limits their applicability in real-time and resource-constrained wireless deployments. In this paper, we investigate whether selective state space models (SSMs) can serve as a hardware-efficient alternative for CSI prediction. We propose MambaCSP, a hybrid-attention SSM architecture that replaces LLM-based prediction backbones with a linear-time Mamba model. To overcome the local-only dependencies of pure SSMs, we introduce lightweight patch-mixer attention layers that periodically inject cross-token attentions, helping with long-context CSI prediction. Extensive MISO-OFDM simulations show that MambaCSP improves prediction accuracy over LLM-based approaches by 9--12\\%, while delivering up to 3.0x higher throughput, 2.6x lower VRAM usage, and 2.9x faster inference. Our results demonstrate that hybrid state space architectures provide a promising direction for scalable and hardware-efficient AI-native CSI prediction.</p>","absKo":"최근 연구들은 attention-based transformer와 large language model (LLM) architecture가 channel state information (CSI) sequence 전반의 장기 temporal dependency를 포착함으로써 강력한 channel state prediction (CSP) 성능을 달성할 수 있음을 보였다. 그러나 이러한 모델은 sequence length에 대해 quadratic scaling을 가지므로 계산 비용, memory 사용량, inference latency가 크게 증가하며, 이는 real-time 및 resource-constrained wireless deployment에서의 적용을 제한한다. 본 논문에서는 selective state space model (SSM)이 CSI prediction을 위한 hardware-efficient alternative가 될 수 있는지 조사한다. 우리는 LLM-based prediction backbone을 linear-time Mamba model로 대체하는 hybrid-attention SSM architecture인 MambaCSP를 제안한다. 순수한 SSM의 local-only dependency를 극복하기 위해, 우리는 주기적으로 cross-token attention을 주입하는 lightweight patch-mixer attention layer를 도입하여 long-context CSI prediction을 돕는다. 광범위한 MISO-OFDM simulation은 MambaCSP가 LLM-based approach보다 prediction accuracy를 9--12\\% 향상시키면서도 throughput은 최대 3.0배 높고, VRAM 사용량은 2.6배 낮으며, inference는 2.9배 빠름을 보여준다. 우리의 결과는 hybrid state space architecture가 scalable하고 hardware-efficient한 AI-native CSI prediction을 위한 유망한 방향임을 입증한다.","link":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=gxwfDntIz5"}];window.dispatchEvent(new CustomEvent("papers-loaded",{detail:"54101"}));